post_text:
Corning Hawks! If you need a physical for athletics, we have a date for you!

Physicals will take place at the high school on August 6th. Please call the nurse at 654-2782 or 654-2784 to set up an appointment. If you need to you can leave a message and they will return your call.

Due to COVID-19 we have some procedures involved in our physicals. Please see below:

1) August 6th from 8 am -12 pm at the high school.
2) Enter through the main doors at the front of the building.
3) Only students will be allowed to enter the building - parents will be asked to wait outside or in their cars.
4) Students must wear a mask, at all times, unless otherwise instructed during the physical.
5) Students will have their temperatures taken and will complete a 4 question screening questionnaire before entering the building.
6) Students will be expected to follow all social distancing guidelines and school protocols explained to them upon arrival.

post_text:
Last Friday Night Lights!

Friday, June 12th will be the last time we light the stadium from 8:20 to 8:40 pm. This will be the last lighting of the year to honor all our students, parents and staff who are currently missing all the activities and community events that the school provides.

In light of the current conditions we must follow all social distancing rules to help in this endeavor: we will not allow congregating on Corning-Painted Post High School grounds.

We advise that you drive by the stadium or drive over the bridge to view the stadium. Do not congregate together. Remember to follow all social distancing rules and to wear your mask when in public, no matter where you are.

Again, there will be no parking on school grounds.

Drive by and celebrate our students, parents and staff as we light our stadium!

Thank your Mr. Austin and Mr. Keeler for the incredible pictures!

post_text: Happy Memorial Day! The Corning Memorial Stadium was dedicated on September 12, 1948, in honor of those men and women who served our country. To say thank you for all those who have served, tonight we will light the stadium at 8:30 pm for 9 minutes and 12 seconds. We want to wish everyone a Happy Memorial Day! Thank you to all that do serve our country. Thank you to all that have given service to our country!

Reminder Corning Hawks: Tonight, May 22nd, the Corning Memorial Stadium will have the lights on! We will light up the stadium from 8:20 to 8:40 pm. We want to honor all our students, parents and staff who are currently missing all the activities and community events that the school provides.

In light of the current conditions we must follow all social distancing rules to help in this endeavor: we will not allow congregating on Corning-Painted Post High School grounds.

We advise that you drive by the stadium or drive over the bridge to view the stadium. Do not congregate together. Remember to follow all social distancing rules and to wear your mask when in public, no matter where you are.

Again, there will be no parking on school grounds.

Drive by and celebrate our students, parents and staff as we light our stadium!

Thank your Mr. Jeremy Austin for the incredible pictures!

Corning Hawks: it is with a heavy heart that we forward the news that the NYSPHSAA has decided to cancel any remaining Winter Championships. This directly impacts our bowling team who had members going to compete at the state tournament.

We are so proud of Meghan Sturdevant who was to represent our Girls Bowling! We are so proud of our Boys Team which included Michael Hoffman-Bellucci, Matthew Hoffman-Bellucci, Brody Amidon, Cameron Kennedy, Isaiah Beschler, Joseph Enderle, Lucas Gwin, and Cory Bigelow! These young men retained the STAC Championship and were heading to States for the 3rd year in a row. What an amazing team!

post_text: Corning Hawk Boys Swimming and Diving at the Elmira invite today. They set 3 Elmira pool records. Cal Bartone in the 100 breaststroke, our 200 medley relay (Palumbo, Bartone, Portwood, McNutt), and our 400 free relay (Hursh, Palumbo, Bartone, McNutt). Our 400 free relay also made the state cut for the first time this season and their time ranks them at 3rd in the state! Awesome job Hawks!
